```

After `ext φ` and `simp_rw`, the goal becomes:
`TestFunction.integralAgainstBilinCLM (ContinuousLinearMap.lsmul ℝ ℝ) μ f φ = TestFunction.integralAgainstBilinCLM (ContinuousLinearMap.lsmul ℝ ℝ) μ f' φ`

Since the integral is the same, the distributions will be the same. The equality of the integrals follows from the fact that `f = f'` almost everywhere with respect to `μ.restrict ↑Ω`, which implies `f = f'` on the support of any test function `φ`.

